title: Strictly Come Dancing 2015 week 4 training & behind-the-scenes
text:
Posted on October 17, 2015 By Pip Ellwood-Hughes Strictly Come Dancing , TV News Credit: BBC/Ray Burmiston/Matt Burlem 
Strictly Come Dancing 2015 continues tonight as the competition enters its fourth week. 
Last weekend the competition said goodbye to Olympic boxer Anthony Ogogo and his partner Oti Mabuse. They found themselves in the bottom two with chef Ainsley Harriott and his partner Natalie Lowe. 
After The Wanted star Jay McGuiness got the first 10 of the series last week for his impressive Jive, the competition has really heated up and the pressure is on tonight. 
Tonight the remaining 13 couples will be dancing to keep their place in the competition. Ahead of tonight’s show the weekly training and behind-the-scenes videos have been released so you can see how the couple’s are getting on.
